{
  "text": "In order for this limit to exist we take a diffusion limit, which requires the ratio of \u2206x 2 and \u2206t to remain constant [CITATION_1] . We also define a continuous version of the annihilation probability, a \u2206 (x, t), where a \u2206 (i\u2206x, n\u2206t) = A(i, n). The \u2206 dependence in the continuous function defines a \u2206 (x, t) as the probability of an annihilation event between t and t + \u2206t. We can then define an annihilation rate as the limit,",
